body:
`preds` is indeed a generator object that cannot be printed on its own. [The Estimator Tutorial](https://www.tensorflow.org/get_started/estimator) demonstrates this:

```python
predictions = list(classifier.predict(input_fn=predict_input_fn))
predicted_classes = [p["classes"] for p in predictions]

print(
    "New Samples, Class Predictions:    {}\n"
    .format(predicted_classes))
```

If you have more issues like this, please post a question on [Stack Overflow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/tagged/tensorflow), which is more suited to individual issues that are not bugs or feature requests. Thanks!
